單車臨界量被視為是一種[[抗議|抗議]]活動，2006年某期《[[紐約客|紐約客]]》（''New Yorker''）雜誌的文章形容[[紐約|紐約]]的單車臨界量為“每個月的政治抗議騎乘活動”，並將之歸類為[[社會運動|社會運動]]。<ref>{{cite news | title=Holy Rollers | first=Ben | last=Mcgrath | date=2006-11-13 | url=http://www.newyorker.com/printables/fact/061113fa_fact | accessdate=2007-09-13 | archive-date=2012-09-04 | archive-url=https://archive.today/20120904154139/http://www.newyorker.com/printables/fact/061113fa_fact | dead-url=no }}</ref>[[英國|英國]]一個發表不少單車臨界量照片與內容的網路雜誌{{tsl|en|Urban75|Urban75}}將這場活動形容為「單車騎士每個月爭取路權的抗議活動」<ref>{{cite web | title=Critical Mass London | publisher=Urban75 | date=2006 | url=http://www.urban75.org/photos/critical | accessdate=2007-09-13 | archive-date=2006-12-31 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061231063118/http://www.urban75.org/photos/critical/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。不過，活動的參與者堅持主張這些活動應該被視為是一種「慶祝」與隨性的群聚，不是抗議或者展示會。<ref>{{cite web | title=Pittsburgh Critical Mass | url=http://pghcriticalmass.org/ | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090928023011/http://www.pghcriticalmass.org/ | archivedate=2009-09-28 | accessdate=2007-09-13 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Critical Mass: Over 260 Arrested in First Major Protest of RNC | date=2004-08-30 | publisher=Democracy Now! | url=http://www.democracynow.org/article.pl?sid=04/08/30/1453256 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071114174744/http://www.democracynow.org/article.pl?sid=04%2F08%2F30%2F1453256 | archivedate=2007-11-14 | accessdate=2017-12-07 }}</ref>這樣子的主張也可以合法地解釋為何這個活動不需要事先向政府單位申請。<ref>{{cite news | title=Critical crackdown | first=Matt | last=Seaton | publisher=The Guardian | date=2005-10-26 | url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/g2/story/0,3604,1600570,00.html | accessdate=2007-09-13 | archive-date=2008-01-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080116120939/http://www.guardian.co.uk/g2/story/0,3604,1600570,00.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=[*BCM*] Hong Kong Critical Mass News | first=Adam | last=Rosi-Kessel | date=2004-08-24